```

## Workflow checklist

For an agent or user to verify the project is in good shape at any
point:

- [ ] `prfaq.md` is frozen (`prereg/prfaq.lock` exists, hash matches)
- [ ] Every active or completed trial has a frozen pre-registration
  (`prereg/PR_<id>.lock` exists, frozen before trial timestamp)
- [ ] `explanation_ledger.md` has at least 2 competing explanations
  per active question (≥1 should be a null / artifact explanation)
- [ ] Every trial in `purposes/` has a complete Analysis section (5
  sub-fields, A0-A5 tier explicit) and a `prereg_diff.py` output
  recorded
- [ ] `decisions.md` records durable state transitions and promotion-relevant
  deviations; ordinary run notes may stay with the tracker or trial artifact
- [ ] Tracking backend or run-note convention is clear before the first
  load-bearing claim
- [ ] Selection, sweep, and failed-run records exist when they affect a
  multiple-testing or promotion judgment
- [ ] Reproducibility 3-tuple recorded for every promotion-eligible
  trial via `scripts/reproducibility_stamp.py` or an equivalent selected
  tracking backend
- [ ] No major deviations from any pre-registration unaddressed (any
  major deviation should have triggered a fresh pre-registration)
- [ ] IMRAD draft started after PR/FAQ freeze (not deferred to the end)

